      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and tremors are common side effects of lithium, but they can also signal a need for a dosage adjustment or a change in your regimen. Since you're already on a prescription, the best course of action is to carefully monitor your symptoms and perhaps try increasing your water intake to help with lithium clearance. If the shaking gets worse, you can't manage it, or the nausea becomes severe, you should definitely call your prescribing physician for a professional assessment.",
